2016-08-25

The diamonds dataset is a dataset that comes built-in with the ggplot2 package in R. It contains measurements on 10 different variables (like price, color, clarity, etc.) for 53,940 different diamonds.

Example

smaller <- diamonds %>% 
  filter(carat <= 2.5)
smaller

We have data about 53940 diamonds. Only 126 are larger than 2.5 carats. The distribution of the remainder is shown below:

smaller %>% 
  ggplot(aes(carat)) + 
  geom_freqpoly(binwidth = 0.01)

Format

It contains three important types of content:

  • An (optional) YAML header surrounded by ---s.
  • Chunks of R code surrounded by ```.
  • Text mixed with simple text formatting like # heading and italics.

Text formatting

italic or italic bold bold code superscript2 and subscript2
